gurmukhi: ਅਜੈ ਹਰੀ ॥ ਅਭੈ ਹਰੀ ॥ ਅਭੇਦ ਹਰੀ ॥ ਅਛੇਦ ਹਰੀ ॥੯॥੫੯॥
transliteration: Ajai Daroo|| Abhai Daroo|| Abhed Daroo|| Achhed Daroo||9||59||
translation: The Lord is Unconquerable. The Lord is Fearless. The Lord’s secrets cannot be known. The Lord is Unassailable. 9.59.

gurmukhi: ਅਖੰਡ ਹਰੀ ॥ ਅਭੰਵ ਹਰੀ ॥ ਅਡੰਡ ਹਰੀ ॥ ਪ੍ਰਚੰਡ ਹਰੀ ॥੧੧॥੬੦॥
transliteration: Akhanndddaroo|| Abhand Daroo|| Adand Daroo|| Prachanndd Daroo||10||60||
translation: The Lord is Indivisible. The Lord cannot be slandered. The Lord cannot be punished. The Lord is Supremenly Glorious.10.60.

gurmukhi: ਅਤੇਵ ਹੂਰੀ ॥ ਅਬੇਵ ਹਰੀ ॥ ਅਜੇਵ ਹਰੀ ॥ ਅਛੇਵ ਹਰੀ ॥੧੧॥੬੧॥
transliteration: Atev Daroo|| Abhev Daroo|| Ajev Daroo|| Achhev Daroo||11||61||
translation: The Lord is extremely Great. The Lord’s mystery cannot be known. The Lord needs no food. The Lord is Invincible. 11.61.

gurmukhi: ਭਜੋ ਹਰੀ ॥ ਥਪੋ ਹਰੀ ॥ ਤਪੋ ਹਰੀ ॥ ਜਪੋ ਹਰੀ ॥੧੨॥੬੨॥
transliteration: Bhajo Daroo|| Thapo Daroo|| Tapo Daroo|| Japo Daroo||12||62||
translation: Meditate on the Lord. Worship the Lord. Perform devotion for the Lord. Repeat the Name of the lord. 12.62.

gurmukhi: ਜਲਸ ਤੁਹੀਂ ॥ ਥਲਸ ਤੁਹੀਂ ॥ ਨਦਿਸ ਤੁਹੀਂ ॥ ਨਦਸ ਤੁਹੀਂ ॥੧੩॥੬੩॥
transliteration: Jalas Tuhoon|| Thalas Tuhoon|| Nadis Tuhoon|| Nadas Tuhoon||13||63||
translation: O Lord! Thou art water. O Lord! Thou art dry land.O Lord! Thou art the stream. O Lord ! Thou art the Ocean. 13.63

gurmukhi: ਬ੍ਰਿਛਸ ਤੁਹੀਂ ॥ ਪਤਸ ਤੁਹੀਂ ॥ ਛਿਤਸ ਤੁਹੀਂ ॥ ੳੁਰਧਸ ਤੁਹੀਂ ॥੧੪॥੬੪॥
transliteration: Brichhas Tuhoon|| Patas Tuhoon|| Chhitas Tuhoon|| Urdhas Tuhoon||14||64||
translation: O Lord! Thou art the tree. O Lord! Thou art the leaf. O Lord ! Thou art the earth. O Lord ! Thou art the sky. 14. 64.

gurmukhi: ਭਜਸ ਤੁਅੰ ॥ ਭਜਸ ਤੁਅੰ ॥ ਰਟਮ ਤੁਅੰ ॥ ਠਟਸ ਤੁਅੰ ॥੧੫॥੬੫॥
transliteration: Bhajas Tuan|| Bhajas Tuan|| Ratas Tuan|| Thatas Tuan||15||65||
translation: O Lord! I meditate on Thee. O Lord! I meditate on Thee.O Lord! I repeat Thy Name. O Lord ! I worship Thee. 15.65.

transliteration: Jimoondtuhoon|| Jamaa Tuhoon|| Makoo Tuhoon|| Makaa Tuhoon||16||66||
translation: O Lord! Thou art the earth. O Lord! Thou art the sky.O Lord ! Thou art the Owner of the house. O Lord! Thou art the house Thyself. 16.66.

transliteration: Abhoo Tuhoon|| Abhai Tuhoon|| Achhodh Tuhoon|| Achhai Tuhoon||17||67||
translation: O Lord! Thou art birthless. O Lord Thou art Fearless.O Lord ! Thou art Untouchabe. O Lord ! Thou art Invincible.17.67.

gurmukhi: ਜਤਸ ਤੁਹੀਂ ॥ ਬ੍ਰਤਸ ਤੁਹੀਂ ॥ ਗਤਸ ਤੁਹੀਂ ॥ ਮਤਸ ਤੁਹੀਂ ॥੧੮॥੬੮॥
transliteration: Jatas Tuhoon|| Bratas Tuhoon|| Gadas Tuhoon|| Matas Tuhoon||18||68||
translation: O Lord! Thou art the celibacy. O Lord! Thou art the means for a virtuous deed. O Lord! Thou art the salvation. O Lord! Thou art the Redemption. 18.68.

transliteration: Tuhoon Tuhoon|| Tuhoon Tuhoon|| Tuhoon Tuhoon|| Tuhoon Tuhoon||19||69||
translation: O Lord! Everything art Thou, Everything Thou art. O Lord! Everything Thou art the salvation. O Lord ! Everything art Thou, Everything Thou art. O Lord! Everything Thou art. O Lord! Everything art Thou, Everything Thou art. 19.69.

transliteration: Tuhoon Tuhoon|| Tuhoon Tuhoon|| Tuhoon Tuhoon|| Tuhoon Tuhoon||20||70||
translation: O Lord! Everything art Thou, Everything Thou art. O Lord! Everything art Thou, Eveything Thou art. O Lord! Everything art Thou, Everything Thou art. O Lord! O Lord! Everything art Thou, Everything Thou art. 20.70.

gurmukhi: ਖੁਕ ਮਲਹਾਰੀ ਗਜ ਗਦਹਾ ਬਿਭੂਤਧਾਰੀ ਗਿਦੂਅਾ ਮਸਾਨ ਬਾਸ ਕਰਿਓ ੲੀ ਖਰਤ ਹੈਂ ॥
transliteration: Khook Malhdaroo Gad Gad-haa Bibhootdhdaroo, Gidooaa Masaan Baas Kario Ee Karat Hain||
translation: If the Lord is realized by eating filth, by besmearing the body with ashes and by residing in he cremation-ground, then the hog eats filth, the elephant and ass get their bodies filled with ashes and the bager resides in the cremation-ground.
